parameters.y: A numeric vector: the number of pups that survived the 21 day lactation.
parameters.n: A numeric vector: the number of pups alive at 4 days.
parameters.group: A factor with levels CTRL and TREAT

description:
Description
“Weil (1970) in Table 1 gives the results from an experiment comprising two treatments. One group of 
16 pregnant female rats was fed a control diet during pregnancy and lactation, the diet of a second group of 16 pregnant 
females was treated with a chemical. For each litter the number n of pups alive at 4 days and the number x 
of pups that survived the 21 day lactation period were recorded.” (Williams, 1975, p. 951).
title: Rats Diet Experiment
reference:
Williams, D.A., 1975. The analysis of binary responses from toxicological experiments
involving reproduction and teratogenicity. Biometrics 31, 949-952.
format: A data frame with 32 observations on the following 3 variables.
